{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_52","type":"agent_message","text":"Plan for the implementation:\n\n1. Add a new surface-wave audit module and CLI that resolve existing `surface_wave` arm plans, expand deterministic sweep points and seeds, execute coupled runs plus representative single-neuron pulse probes, and write stable local artifacts.\n2. Generate deterministic review outputs under a dedicated processed directory: top-level `summary.json` / `report.md` / `index.html`, plus per-run summaries, trace archives, and lightweight SVG trace panels.\n3. Compute compact diagnostics and run classification from stable metrics: finite-value checks, pulse energy/amplitude growth, wavefront-detection status, coupled dynamic range, spatial contrast, and coupling-event sanity.\n4. Add docs, config/Makefile integration, and a smoke fixture test that runs a small sweep end-to-end and asserts output paths plus expected diagnostic fields.\n5. Run the targeted smoke test, then `make test`, and finish by staging the ticket changes and creating a normal commit."}}
